  "sections": {
    "Description": "Much like theHornet, Mosquitoes are 2-health flying Vek that have a weak melee attack. Unlike the Hornet, however, Mosquitoes have one less point of movement and applySmoketo the targeted tile at the end of their movement.\nMosquitoes cannot spawn on an island with any other flying Vek (Hornet,Moth) other than the island's Psion.",
    "Strategy": "As Smoke does not inhibit movement, it's often manageable just by moving away. However, Smoke in a poor location can sometimes cause problems, and can be particularly dangerous in combination with webbing enemies. Overall, Mosquitoes should not be considered an especially high threat enemy, and their lower health makes them easy to kill. They do have high flying movement though, so it's important to neutralize them before they are capable of moving too far away from your Mechs."
  },
  "full_text": "Mosquito\nDetails\nHealth\n2\nMove\n4\nSystems\nSmoked Tentacles\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nSmoke the target, preparing to whip it for 1 damage.\nSpecial\nFlying\n: Flying units can move over any terrain tile.\nThe\nMosquito\nis a flying\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\nintroduced in the Advanced Edition. They are only present if Advanced Enemies are turned on at the start of a new timeline.\nDescription\n[\n]\nMuch like the\nHornet\n, Mosquitoes are 2-health flying Vek that have a weak melee attack. Unlike the Hornet, however, Mosquitoes have one less point of movement and apply\nSmoke\nto the targeted tile at the end of their movement.\nMosquitoes cannot spawn on an island with any other flying Vek (Hornet,\nMoth\n) other than the island's Psion.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nAs Smoke does not inhibit movement, it's often manageable just by moving away. However, Smoke in a poor location can sometimes cause problems, and can be particularly dangerous in combination with webbing enemies. Overall, Mosquitoes should not be considered an especially high threat enemy, and their lower health makes them easy to kill. They do have high flying movement though, so it's important to neutralize them before they are capable of moving too far away from your Mechs.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
